          <p class="text-yellow-700">
            Always consult with your healthcare provider before starting cold plunging, especially if you have cardiovascular conditions, are pregnant, or have other health concerns.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-gray-800 mb-4">Beginner Protocol</h3>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-gray-600 mb-6">
          <li>Start with cold showers (30 seconds at the end of your regular shower)</li>
          <li>Gradually increase cold exposure time over 2-3 weeks</li>
          <li>Move to ice baths or cold plunge tubs when comfortable</li>
          <li>Begin with 1-2 minutes in 60°F water</li>
          <li>Slowly work down to 50°F as your tolerance builds</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-gray-800 mb-4">Best Practices</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
          <li>Never plunge alone - always have someone nearby</li>
          <li>Focus on controlling your breathing</li>
          <li>Exit immediately if you feel dizzy or unwell</li>
          <li>Warm up gradually after your session</li>
          <li>Track your cycle - some women find certain phases more suitable</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

